Police in Katsina yesterday presented four women and their children rescued from bandits in a forest in Malumfashi council of the state. They also displayed the bodies of two suspects killed in two operations. Spokesman of the command Gambo Isah also said one AK47 rifle and 150 rustled animals were recovered from the hoodlums.   2023: Vote for trusted leaders, says clergy     Accord Party working with external bodies to win…     Yiaga Africa trains 74 legislative aides   Isah said the DPO in charge of Malumfashi reacted to a distress call that hoodlums had attacked Gandu Karfi community where they abducted four women and went away with over 150 cows and sheep. He said, “The DPO led a team of policemen, ambushed the terrorists and killed one of them. They also recovered one AK47 rifle, four rounds of ammunition, 80 cows and 70 sheep.” - Advertisement - Another suspected bandit was killed in Kankara where the police team encountered one more gang of gunmen, Isah said.   SPONSORED